# Walkthrough - Performance Monitoring & SOLID Refactoring

This walkthrough documents the changes made to resolve the `std::queue<unique_ptr<RequestWrap>>::front()` assertion failure reported in the `libcamerasrc` GStreamer element.

## Changes Made

### 1. Camera Access Synchronization
Added `std::mutex camera_mutex_` to [StreamPipeline](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#17-35) to ensure that `camera_.read()` and `camera_.release()` do not conflict.
- **[cameraLoop](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#364-424)**: Checks the `is_streaming_` flag under the lock but performs the blocking [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) outside the lock to avoid deadlocks.
- **[stopStreaming](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#148-190)**: Acquires the lock before calling `camera_.release()` to ensure it unblocks any pending [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) safely and prevents new [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) calls from starting.

### 2. GStreamer Pipeline Optimization
Updated the `libcamerasrc` capture pipeline to be more resilient to buffer starvation:
- Increased `max-size-buffers` from **3** to **10** for all queue elements.
- Enabled `leaky=downstream` on queues to prevent backpressure from blocking the internal `libcamera` threads.
- Increased `appsink`'s `max-buffers` to **2** for better decoupling.

### 3. Graceful Shutdown Sequence
Adjusted the termination sequence in [stopStreaming()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#148-190):
1. Set `is_streaming_` to `false`.
2. Release camera resources (`camera_.release()`) to unblock the reading thread.
3. Join the threads.
4. Clean up remaining queues.

## Validation Results
- **Deadlock Mitigation**: Verified that the locking strategy avoids holding the mutex during the blocking [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) call, preventing a deadlock during shutdown.
- **Logic Verification**: The synchronization ensures that `libcamerasrc` internal state is not torn down while a user-initiated [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) is actively processing a `Request` object.

## SOLID Refactoring: Performance Monitoring

To address violation of the **Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)**, the performance measuring and logging logic was extracted from [StreamPipeline](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#17-35) into a dedicated utility.

### 1. [PerformanceMonitor](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/util/PerformanceMonitor.h#19-24) Utility Class
Created [src/util/PerformanceMonitor.h](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/util/PerformanceMonitor.h) to encapsulate:
- Timer management and moving average calculations.
- Automatic periodic logging (default 5s).
- Specialized formatting for different units (MS, US, FPS).

### 2. De-coupled [StreamPipeline](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#17-35)
[StreamPipeline](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp#17-35) now focuses solely on orchestration. All timing and logging logic is delegated to monitor instances:
- `perf_ai_`: Records AI latency (ms).
- `perf_pre_`: Records pre-processing time (us).
- `perf_fps_cap_`: Measures camera capture rate.
- `perf_fps_proc_`: Measures processing loop throughput.

### 3. Benefits
- **Readability**: [StreamPipeline.cpp](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp) is significantly shorter and easier to read.
- **Maintainability**: Monitoring logic can be updated in one place without touching the core pipeline.
- **Consistency**: All performance logs follow the same formatted structure.
